sql:
SELECT network_name 
FROM networks
WHERE DATE(updated_at) = '2023-01-01';

SELECT molecular_weight 
FROM compounds 
WHERE type = 'nucleotide';

SELECT DISTINCT c.compound_name 
FROM compounds c 
WHERE c.compound_id IN (
    SELECT i.to_compound_id 
    FROM interactions i
);

external_knowledge:
- "Kings of the molecular world" refers to the compounds with the highest molecular weight in each taxonomic classification; 
- "Molecular blueprints" refers to the molecular formula of the compounds; 
- "Scepters" refers to the annotations of the compounds.

sql:
SELECT molecular_formula 
FROM compounds 
WHERE molecular_weight = (SELECT MAX(molecular_weight) FROM compounds);
